  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a dApp developer, I want to query a Beacon node so that i can retrieve information like node identity, genesis details,... \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* HTTP calls from a Javascript library in browser work\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. perform any http call on the Beacon node API from a Javascript library on a browser.\r\n\r\nExample using `axios`:\r\n```javascript\r\nconst response = await axios.get('http://127.0.0.1:5051/eth/v1/node/identity');\r\nconsole.log(response);\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** \r\nHTTP requests work normally.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** \r\nHTTP requests are failing with this error:\r\n```\r\nAccess to XMLHttpRequest at 'http://127.0.0.1:5051/eth/v1/node/identity' from origin 'http://localhost:8080'\r\nhas been blocked by CORS policy: No 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin' header is present on the requested resource.\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Frequency:**\r\nAlways\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: `teku/v20.11.0+9-g49a228e/osx-x86_64/adoptopenjdk-java-11`\r\n* Java version: `openjdk 11.0.2 2019-01-15`\r\n* OS Name & Version: `Mac OS Catalina 10.15.5 (19F101)`\r\n* Kernel Version: `Darwin abdelhamids-mbp.home 19.5.0 Darwin Kernel Version 19.5.0: Tue May 26 20:41:44 PDT 2020; root:xnu-6153.121.2~2/RELEASE_X86_64 x86_64`\r\n",
